b'A lot of people think Spotify is just for music, but there is a whole world of podcasts with many different genres and content and personalities, you should definitely try listening!\n\nI love visual content pero iba din yung effect when you zone in on just your sense of hearing.'

b'Tbh my favorite local pod is Ang Walang Kwentang Podcast! I love "learning" podcasts which is why I gravitate towards creating that kind of content, but when I need a break from seriousness, ito talaga go-to ko.'

b'I personally am a huge podcast listener and have been wanting to join the platform for years now, but I just waited for when the time is right. \n\nMy favorite podcasters are Brene Brown, Adam Grant, TED podcasts, or usually I search for the name of a guest I wanna listen to!'

b'To maximize the interviews I get to do, I usually upload a shorter, more fast-paced video version on my YouTube page, usually 10 to 15 minutes, while the longer, more deep dive conversation is on the podcast, usually 20 to even 45 minutes!\n\nhttps://t.co/9s7MBdwPGx'

b'Just this year, from the book and YouTube channel, I finally joined the podcasting world with #PaanoBaTo: The Podcast! It has been a challenge but also a lot of fun creating podcast-only episodes!\n\nhttps://t.co/AYoxPpdWeu'

b"To everyone curious about what a podcast is like, basically imagine consuming the content of a YouTube or IGTV video, but this time its AUDIO only. So you can do chores, exercise, some even work while listening! It's free to listen to episodes on platforms such as Spotify."
